  "text": "Effects of celastrol on activities of cellular proteasome and finding of proteasome catalytic subunit b1 as a direct target of celastrol. To examine the effect of celastrol on cellular proteasome activities, cells were treated with celastrol at different concentrations for 24 h, harvested, washed with PBS and then lysed with proteasome activity assay buffer (10 mM Tris-HCL, pH 7.8, 5 mM adenosine triphosphate, 0.5 mM dithiothreitol and 5 mM MgCL 2 6H 2 O) for 30 min at 4 1C. The homogenate was then centrifuged at 15 000 Â g for 30 min at 4 1C. The supernatant was collected as whole-cell extract and the protein content in the supernatant was measured with the Bradford reagent. The enzymatic activity of cellular proteasome in cell lysate was measured similar to previous reports. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Detailed information can be found in Supplementary Materials and Methods.",
